importables:
elementalcomponents -> has components of elements and amino acids
generalfunctions -> has several functions used across various parts of the workflow
sequencetools -> has protein sequence handling functions

overhead:
execution -> organizes files, converts to mzML, and runs the main script
main -> executes data processing

database preparation:
isotopelibrary -> generate isotopic distributions, and some subisotopomer calculations

~
Improvements to this file:
 - explain how the data from each called function is organized for it to be used later
 - given an origin/destination of each saved variable

~
data processing: in order of their calling

linemodel: implemented, core
 - sorts signals into useable groups, links ms2 hits to groups on the fly
 - makes signal data indexable to be used for the rest of the processing

distributionassembly: implemented, core
 - takes the information accumulated via linemodel and groups line signals into isotopic distributions
 - ranks potential distributions and discerns the best possible ones

chargehandling: implemented, core
 - finalizes distributions from the previous file, organizes and saves them
 - looks for matching charge-states across the prior determined isotopic distributions, outputs the accumulated information

scanmatching: core
 - matching lines to scans and vice versa
 - estimating intensity proportions across all ms1 lines withinin an ms2 window, and their charges
 - consolidating analytes found from distributionmatchpairing into:
    > linesofscans, scansoflines, scansbyanalyte, spectrabysampling, scanwindowbounds, analytefragmentbounds, and so on

distributionmatching: core
 - this is matching library-generated ms1 distributions to any and all found ms1 distributions
 - outputs matching formulas of library distributions, and the position within the library distribution relative to each matched line

differencemining: experimental, not yet implemented
 - looking for common distribution distances of matched to non-matched [major masses (high points) of] ms1 distributions

subformulalinegrouping: core
 - reducing complexity of the ms2 search space by tracking redundant fragment probability distributions
 - grouping subformulas, sequences, and carbon composition of matched lines for final fragment matching

fragmentdeconvolution: core
 - deconvoluting charges from every ms2 scan

groupfragmentation: core
 - generating fragment distributions from the groups in subformulalinegrouping and searching them across deconvoluted ms2 spectra

fragmentfileorganizing: core
 - minor processing of the groupfragmentation output

entropy -> break clustering
the break clusters will provide a second layer of entropy via pattern recongition
